p:
On the 6th day of the evaluation for the test carried out using 
 O. basilicum, the 120 μL dose was able to kill 24.43 ± 4.06% of the initial insect population, significantly greater (F = 2.78; df = 5.18; 
 p = 0.049) than the mortality obtained by rest of doses evaluated. Meanwhile, on the 8th day, the 60 μL and 120 μL doses were able to kill more than 50% of the adult insects, being significantly higher (F = 9.04; df = 5.18; 
 p < 0.0001) than the control achieved by 24, 12, and 6 μL doses.
